### Reset Password (Requires Authentication)
# This endpoint allows users to reset their own password
# The user must be authenticated and provide their current password

POST http://localhost:3000/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "your_current_password",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePassword123!"
}

### Notes:
# 1. Replace {{authToken}} with your actual JWT token (obtained from login)
# 2. Replace "your_current_password" with your actual current password
# 3. The new password must meet these requirements:
#    - At least 8 characters long
#    - Maximum 128 characters
# 4. Only the authenticated user can reset their own password
# 5. The current password must be correct for the reset to succeed
# 6. This endpoint is in the auth module for better organization 